sql:
SELECT title, year
FROM publications
ORDER BY year DESC;

SELECT journal, AVG(year) AS average_year
FROM publications
GROUP BY journal;

external_knowledge:
- "spring of 2023" refers to publications with an author_year including 2023;
- "journey of those that have blossomed" metaphorically refers to identifying publications published in or citing those published in 2023;
- "ripple effects across the academic seas" refers to indirect citations;
- "identity, blooming season, type, and life stage" refer to pub_id, publication_date, publication_type, and publication_status;
- "depth of their roots, the breadth of their canopy, the clarity of their message, the originality of their leaves, and the scholarly rigor they embody" refer to metrics such as S, B, E, I, C, D, O, SR, h_index, g_index, and citation_count;
- "the myriad voices that speak through them" refers to citation counts from different types;
- "reverse chronological order" means ordering the publication_date in descending order.
